   "cell_type": "raw",
   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Advanced Data Exploration and Text Normalization\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"This notebook explains the full preprocessing stage for Assignment 3.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"We focus on three goals:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Explore the raw text collection for quality issues.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Build two normalization views (semantic and structural).\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Quantify how normalization changes the feature space.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Why two normalization paths?\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Clustering benefits from strong semantic cleaning:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Remove HTML, punctuation, and id-like codes.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Remove stop words.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Apply morphology normalization.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Anomaly detection benefits from structure retention:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Keep punctuation markers and odd symbol bursts.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Keep token patterns that may indicate corruption.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"from pathlib import Path\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import pandas as pd\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from data_mining_assignment.core.data_io import ArticleDataset\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from data_mining_assignment.tasks.exploration import compare_normalization_variants, summarize_corpus\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from data_mining_assignment.tasks.preprocessing import TextNormalizer\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"project_root_path = Path.cwd().parent\\n\",\n",
    "    \"articles_csv_path = project_root_path / \\\"data\\\" / \\\"articles.csv\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"article_dataset = ArticleDataset(input_csv_path=articles_csv_path)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"articles_data_frame = article_dataset.load_articles()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"raw_texts = articles_data_frame[\\\"text\\\"].tolist()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"articles_data_frame.head()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Raw corpus diagnostics\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"The next cell measures signs of noise such as HTML tags and symbol-heavy lines.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"corpus_summary = summarize_corpus(raw_texts)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"corpus_summary\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Generate normalization variants\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"`TextNormalizer` creates two views from the same raw texts:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `clustering_texts`: aggressive semantic cleaning.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- `anomaly_texts`: structural markers preserved.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"text_normalizer = TextNormalizer()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"normalized_text_bundle = text_normalizer.normalize_for_both_tasks(raw_texts)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"preview_data_frame = pd.DataFrame(\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    {\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"raw\\\": raw_texts[:3],\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"clustering_view\\\": normalized_text_bundle.clustering_texts[:3],\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"anomaly_view\\\": normalized_text_bundle.anomaly_texts[:3],\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    }\\n\",\n",
    "    \")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"preview_data_frame\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Quantitative normalization impact\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"A large token reduction usually means less noise and better cluster signal.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"clustering_comparison = compare_normalization_variants(\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    raw_texts=raw_texts,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    normalized_texts=normalized_text_bundle.clustering_texts,\\n\",\n",
    "    \")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"anomaly_comparison = compare_normalization_variants(\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    raw_texts=raw_texts,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    normalized_texts=normalized_text_bundle.anomaly_texts,\\n\",\n",
    "    \")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"pd.DataFrame([clustering_comparison, anomaly_comparison], index=[\\\"clustering\\\", \\\"anomaly\\\"])\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Next step\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"After this notebook, run the pipeline scripts.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"The pipeline now automatically uses these dual normalization paths before clustering and anomaly detection.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  }\n",
    " ],\n",
